[normal]City &amp; Guilds is a leading vocational awarding organisation for work-based qualifications, committed to offering high quality qualifications across a wide range of industrial sectors, 
[normal]through 8500 colleges and training providers worldwide
[normal]. 
[normal]We value the provision of qualifications to a high standard and support 
[normal]any
[normal] work to ensure 
[normal]these 
[normal]standards through the strategic regulation of 
[normal]awarding organisation
[normal]s and qualifications.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Two million people every year take City &amp; Guilds qualifications, which span levels from basic skills to the highest levels of professional achievement, and are designed to help people gai
[normal]n the skills employers’ value. 
[normal]City &amp; Guilds is also a major innovator in the field of electro
[normal]nic assessment (e-assessment). 
[normal]More than four million on-line tests have been taken by candidates entering fo
[normal]r City &amp; Guilds qualifications.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We welcome the opportunity to provide comment
[normal]s
[normal] to this 
[normal]call for evidence and will refer specifically to areas of the Bill affecting education and training. We
[normal] look forward to working with 
[normal]the Joint Committee
[normal] on further developments.
